    "A variant of this approach has also been applied in the AlphaGo architecture 25 to encode symmetries of a Go board.",
    "In our specific implementation, we set G = D 2 = fid, $, l, $lg, the dihedral group.",
    "Exploiting D 2 -invariance allows us to encode quadrant symmetries.",
    "Each element of the D 2 group encodes the presence of vertical or horizontal reflections of the input football pitch.",
    "Under these transformations, the pitch is assumed completely symmetric, and hence many predictions, such as which player receives the corner kick, or takes a shot from it, can be safely assumed unchanged."
